added.title: Thanksgiving
added.description: When Raven's father Trigon shows up for Thanksgiving dinner, Robin's seating plan isn't the only thing that gets ruined.

added.title: Real Boy Adventures
added.description: When he transforms into "Fleshy Guy," Cyborg discovers the joy and pain of being human.

added.title: The Cruel Giggling Ghoul
added.description: The Titans go to an amusement park to see LeBron James but instead help solve a mystery.

added.title: Snuggle Time
added.description: When yet another crime alert interrupts their relaxation, the Titans decide to become villains and do whatever they want.

added.title: The Real Orangins!
added.description: Robin tries again to tell the real origin story of the Teen Titans.

added.title: The Recipe
added.description: Gumball and Darwin discover the secret behind Anton's immortality. Anton's little toasty body disintegrates during a swim class. When Gumball and Darwin see Anton the next day, as good as new, they set out to discover his secret. It turns out that his parents use a special formula to bake new Antons when necessary. So the kids test it out at home and end up baking a clone army whose leader - Ant-one - wants to destroy Anton and take over the world.

added.title: The Saint
added.description: Gumball doesn't believe anyone could really be as nice as Alan and sets out to find his breaking point. Alan is so good-natured that Gumball feels compelled to make him lose his temper. Despite turning the whole school against him, destroying his relationship with Carmen and even selling his parents, Alan remains understanding and happy. Defeated, Gumball and Darwin decide to adopt Alan's positive attitude to see if they can be more like Alan.Gumball and Darwin help Anais make up an imaginary friend who turns out to be all too real. Anais throws a party but no-one shows up as she has no friends or social skills. Gumball and Darwin help Anais make up an imaginary friend who, much to all their surprise, appears in front of them. Gumball and Darwin teach Anais and her new friend how to become friends but realize he might not be so imaginary after all.

added.title: The Safety
added.description: Darwin watches a Health and Safety video and gets carried away. When Mr Small shows a health and safety video in class, Darwin becomes obsessed with the idea of keeping the Wattersons safe. He tries to protect them from the world around them and soon Darwin's over-protective control-freakery spreads to every corner of Elmore. The Wattersons have no choice but to overthrow his despotic regime.

added.title: The Society
added.description: Gumball is convinced there is a Secret Society in school and he wants in. Things aren't going Gumball's way at school so he assumes there must be a Secret Society that gives preferential treatment to its own members. He tries everything to uncover this non-existent society, making everyone's lives miserable in the process. Eventually, in an attempt to restore some peace, the pupils and teachers decide to give him exactly what he wants.

added.title: The Spoiler
added.description: Can Gumball and Darwin get through a whole week without somebody ruining the movie they're planning to see? Gumball and Darwin have spent all their pocket money, so will have to wait until the following weekend to see "The Screamening." It"s the scariest film of the year. The only problem is everyone else has seen it, and won't stop talking about it. Gumball is determined to avoid all spoilers. Will he succeed?

added.title: Cousin of the Creek
added.description: Craig takes his cousin, Bryson, to the Creek, and accidentally starts a water balloon war.

added.title: Stink Bomb
added.description: An accidental stink bomb explosion causes the kids to evacuate the Creek, but Craig takes it upon himself to rescue those left behind in the stench.

added.title: The Haunted Dollhouse
added.description: Craig and his friends find themselves being followed by a creepy doll and its haunted dollhouse.

added.title: Creek Daycare
added.description: Craig and his sister, Jessica, try their hand at running the daycare at the Creek.

added.title: Sleepover at JP's
added.description: JP invites his friends over for a sleepover, but it happens to be on the night of a huge game of Flashlight Tag in the Creek!

added.title: Tree Buds
added.description: Vic and Val build a treehouse and Val dismisses Vic with a frivolous task so he can build the treehouse exactly how he wants. But when Vic returns unknowingly with a branch from El Arbol Vampiro, Val's perfect treehouse turns into a nightmare!

added.title: The Lonely Haunts Club 2: Doll Island
added.description: In order to prove their bravery, V&V head to a haunted island to retrieve a special doll, but Charlene and Pineapple are intent on getting it first.

added.title: Cat-Pocalypse
added.description: When Vic gets sick and is stuck in his room, he spies on Pineapple and becomes convinced that Pineapple is creating an army of zombie cats. Val agrees and the two become obsessed with stopping Pineapple before it's too late!

added.title: El Silbon
added.description: Victor sets up a haunted corn maze, but the town kids think it's lame. Vic decides to make the maze scarier by enlisting the help of El Silbon (The Whistler) to really scare the kids, but El Silbon has plans of his own.

added.title: On Nagual Hill
added.description: Vic & Val take over a forest hill and build an epic waterslide, disturbing the plants and animals that normally inhabit it. But when a Nagual (a human with the power to transform into animals) transforms Vic into a chicken and Val into a donkey, they learn to sympathize with the animals and understand the world a bit more.

added.title: Hot Sauce
added.description: A quest for their favorite hot sauce causes the Bears to get involved with a sting operation.

added.title: The Limo
added.description: To help distract Panda from his girl problems, Grizz and Ice Bear treat him to a ride in a limo.

added.title: Fire!
added.description: Grizz's quick thinking prevents a potential wild fire, but the praise he receives from doing so quickly goes to his head.

added.title: Ranger Norm
added.description: When Tabes leaves for a conference, the Bears have to deal with her substitute, Ranger Norm.

added.title: Cousin Jon
added.description: When the Bears attend Chloe's family reunion, they fall victim to the mischievous pranks of Chloe's cousin, Jon.

added.title: Bridge Out
added.description: After an overpass collapses on the highway, Team Tennyson is in a traffic jam along with Simon Sez and family. But when Ben and Simon team up to tackle the gridlock together, Simon only makes matters much, much worse.

added.title: Beach Heads
added.description: After traveling to Tampa Beach, Florida, Team Tennyson hopes to get some much-needed rest & relaxation, but the tempests without a temper, the Weatherheads, have other plans that Ben must thwart: to build a new beach base!

added.title: Cyber Slammers
added.description: At Biggie Box Japan, Ben waits in an epic line for the release of the latest Sumo Slammers video game, Cyber Slammers, but Ben must save the store not from game-hungry customers, but from Steam Smythe, who wants to retro-fit a massive mech with steam punk powers!

added.title: LaGrange Muraille
added.description: While visiting China, Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max take a trek to the Great Wall, but their adventure is nearly ruined by daredevils LaGrange and Vin Ethanol trying to jump the international monument, and Ben must hop into the Rustbuggy to chase away the fast and furious foes.

added.title: El Club de Los Solitarios 2, La Isla de las Munecas
added.description: Para probar su valentía, Victor y Valentino se dirigen a una isla embrujada para recuperar una muñeca especial, pero Charlene y Piña están decididos a obtenerla antes que ellos.

added.title: Gatocalipsis
added.description: Cuando Vic se enferma y debe reposar en su cuarto, espía a Piña y queda convencido de que está creando un ejército de gatos zombis. Val está de acuerdo con él y ambos se obsesionan con detener a Piña antes de que sea demasiado tarde.

added.title: La Casa del Arbol
added.description: Vic y Val construyen una casa en el árbol, y Val se libra de Vic con una tarea sin importáncia para construir la casa exactamente como quiere. Pero cuando Vic regresa y trae, sin saberlo, una rama del Árbol Vampiro, la casa del árbol perfecta de Val se convierte en una pesadilla.

added.title: El Silbon
added.description: Víctor arma un laberinto de maíz embrujado, pero los chicos del pueblo creen que es muy malo. Vic decide hacer que el laberinto sea más aterrador con la ayuda de El Silbón para asustar de verdad a los chicos, pero El Silbón tiene sus propios planes.

added.title: En la colina Nahual
added.description: Vic y Val se apoderan de la colina de un bosque y construyen un tobogán de agua épico que perturba a las plantas y animales que solían habitar allí. Pero cuando un nahual (un humano con el poder de transformarse en animales) transforma a Vic en un pollo y a Val en un burro, ambos aprenden a empatizar con los animales y a entender el mundo un poco más.

added.title: Drawn To Rhythm: Lorenzo
added.description: Cartoon Network is celebrating Hispanic Heritage Month with another installment of "Drawn To" that showcases kids who honor their Hispanic and Latino heritage as they are drawn to rhythm. In this piece, Lorenzo tells us about his passion for reggaetón music and soccer.

added.title: Drawn To Rhythm: Jayleen
added.description: Cartoon Network is celebrating Hispanic Heritage Month with another installment of "Drawn To" that showcases kids who honor their Hispanic and Latino heritage as they are drawn to rhythm. In this piece, Jayleen shows us some of the eight different dance styles she can do, including bachata and cumbia.

added.title: Arcade Mania
added.description: Steven takes the Crystal Gems to Funland Arcade where Garnet learns the allure of video games.

added.title: Giant Woman
added.description: During a mission to the Sky Spire, Steven tries to convince Amethyst and Pearl to fuse together and become a giant woman.

added.title: Lars and the Cool Kids
added.description: Steven and Lars get to hang out with the cool kids in town, but their teenage shenanigans get them into magical trouble.

added.title: Steven the Sword Fighter
added.description: Pearl tries to teach Steven the art of sword-fighting using a holographic version of himself.

added.title: Beach Party
added.description: After a battle damages Fish Stew Pizza, Steven throws a cookout at the Temple to mend the relationship between Pizza family and the Crystal Gems.

added.title: Zing Your Heart Out
added.description: When Adorabat starts to aggressively heckle everyone with her new zing power, she threatens the entire kingdom.

added.title: Little Homeschool
added.description: Welcome to Little Homeschool, a place on earth where Gems from all over the universe can come learn how to live together peacefully! But there's one Gem who refuses to attend.

added.title: The Future
added.description: Steven is finally ready to move on.

added.title: Dawn of the Donut
added.description: Dr. Fox's plans to deliver donuts all over the Unikingdom are sidetracked by Unikitty's reluctance to follow instructions.

added.title: P.L.O.T. Device 2: Beyond the Bored Dome
added.description: Dr. Fox reprograms the P.L.O.T. Device to only generate boring events, but the gang can't help but add drama and excitement to every scenario.

added.title: The New Nemesis
added.description: When Hawkodile discovers his old enemy Eagleator has a new nemesis in his life, the gang do all they can to get Hawk back on his foe's radar.

added.title: Baby Caterpillar
added.description: Unikitty takes in a radioactive caterpillar and raises it like a baby, unaware of the havoc it will wreak as a full-grown adult.

added.title: Borrowed
added.description: Richard discovers his library books have been borrowed by Master Frown and sets off on a crazed mission to return the books before they're overdue.

added.title: Deep Space Vacation
added.description: When Gar lets KO and Enid take a vacation to outer  space, they get more than they bargained for.

added.title: Radical Rescue
added.description: Rad is forced to reconsider his identity when KO starts taking on some of his traits.

added.title: Let's Get Shadowy
added.description: KO teams up with an unlikely ally to take on an old foe.

added.title: Special Delivery
added.description: Enid and Rad go on a road trip to deliver a package.

added.title: Presenting Joe Cuppa
added.description: KO tries to help his favorite comedian, Joe Cuppa.

added.title: Sister Sitter
added.description: When Blossom and Bubbles get sick, Buttercup volunteers to take care of them for the day.

added.title: Presidential Punchout
added.description: When Morbucks enters the Student Body President race, Blossom sinks to her level to secure the win.

added.title: Fashion Forward
added.description: When the Fashionistas launch a new line of brainwashing clothing, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls to stop the fashion trend before it's too late.

added.title: In the Garden of Good and Eddie
added.description: When the girls try a quick-fix on their neglected veggie garden, they are left with a giant, mooching tomato worm they must care for.

added.title: Road Trippin'
added.description: Realizing her and the Professor don't have much in common, Bubbles schedules a road trip with just the two of them.

added.title: Camp Fear
added.description: When a race of alien mushrooms takes over a summer camp, Ben discovers a whole new alien to battle the menace.

added.title: Tough Luck
added.description: Gwen's Lucky Girl powers return when she buys a magical stone at a magic convention in Las Vegas. However, Hex is after the same stone, and after his niece breaks him out of prison, the two set off to retrieve the stone.

added.title: Ghostfreaked Out
added.description: Ben's internal demons get externalized when Ghostfreak escapes from his watch and becomes a full fledged being on his own. The renegade alien then realizes he needs to meld with Ben's DNA in order to survive.

added.title: Catfight
added.description: The princesses Looma and Attea are at odds over who gets to marry Ben!

added.title: The Vengers
added.description: Billy Billions, Kangaroo Kommando, and Captain Nemesis team up to take down Ben, and claim his place as protector of Bellwood?!?

added.title: The Rooters of All Evil
added.description: Meet the Rooters, the Black Ops wing of the Plumbers from the Null Void. They've come looking for someone close to Ben, and they mean business!

added.title: No Honor Among Bros
added.description: Rook is under the influence of Fistrick's "bro" essence, and starts to act like a bro. Can he and Ben infiltrate an alien fight club to claim the Golden Fist? (Introducing Slix Vigma, alien promoter.)

added.title: Weapon XI Part 1
added.description: Kevin and Argit attempt to warn the amalgam kids about the Rooters intentions meanwhile Ben, Rook, and Gwen set off to find Kevin and land themselves in the Null Void!

added.title: Mystery Dungeon
added.description: Ice King, NEPTR, Tree Trunks, Shelby and Lemongrab are trapped inside a mysterious dungeon and must work together to free themselves.

added.title: Los Verdaderos Orijanes
added.description: Robin trata de contar la verdadera historia del origen de los Jóvenes Titanes.

added.title: Little Dude
added.description: While Finn and Jake go swimming, Finn's hat magically comes to life!

added.title: James Baxter the Horse
added.description: Finn and Jake meet a horse with the power to make sad people happy.

added.title: One Last Job
added.description: Jake Jr. gets mixed up with some bad eggs and Jake has to reunite with his old gang for one last job to save him.

added.title: Play Date
added.description: Sick and tired of babysitting Ice King while the Ice Kingdom is being rebuilt, Finn and Jake call up an old friend to hang out with their annoying houseguest, Abracadaniel.

added.title: Salsa Picante
added.description: La búsqueda de su salsa picante favorita hace que los Osos se involucren en una operación de picadura.

added.title: La Limosna
added.description: Para ayudar a Panda a distraerse de sus problemas románticos, Pardo y Polar le regalan un paseo en limosina.

added.title: Fuego
added.description: La rapidez de pensamiento de Pardo evita un posible incendio incontrolado, pero los elogios que recibe hacen que se vuelva pedante muy rápidamente.

added.title: El Guardia Norm
added.description: Cuando Tabes se va a una conferencia, los Osos deben lidiar con su reemplazo, el guardabosques Norm.

added.title: El primo Jon
added.description: Cuando los Osos asisten a una reunión con la familia de Chloe, se convierten en víctimas de Jon, el travieso primo de Chloe.

added.title: Bloqueo de Tránsito
added.description: Cuando un paso elevado colapsa sobre la autopista, el equipo Tennyson queda varado en un embotellamiento junto con Simon Sez y familia. Pero cuando Ben y Simon se alían para enfrentar juntos al atasco, Simon solo consigue que las cosas sean mucho, pero mucho peores.

added.title: Cabeza de Playa
added.description: Después de viajar a Tampa Beach, Florida, el equipo Tennyson espera poder descansar y relajarse, pero las tempestades sin temperamento, los Climáticos, tienen otros planes que Ben debe frustrar: iconstruir una nueva base en la playa!

added.title: Cyber Luchadores
added.description: En Biggie Box Japón, Ben espera en una fila épica el lanzamiento de Cyber Luchadores, el último videojuego de Luchadores de Sumo. Pero muy pronto, Ben debe salvar la tienda: no de los clientes ansiosos por comprar el juego sino de Vapor Smythe, ique quiere modernizar un mecanismo gigantesco con sus vandálicos poderes de vapor!

added.title: La Grange Muralla
added.description: Ben, Gwen y el abuelo Max hacen un viaje a la Gran Muralla, pero su aventura por poco termina arruinada por los temerarios LaGrange y Vin Etanol, que intentan saltar sobre el monumento internacional. Ben debe subirse al Rustbuggy para ahuyentar a los enemigos.

added.title: Big Ben 10
added.description: Cuando Ben y su familia viajan a Londres para visitar el legendario Big Ben, los hermanos Bicho están allí para darles la bienvenida, obviamente con un nuevo plan escandalosamente exagerado: iencoger la campana del Big Ben para robarla!

added.title: Bird Boy Man
added.description: Sumo discovers an injured roadrunner, names him Hot Sauce, and nurses him back to health. The two become inseparable pals, but Sumo learns that a wild animal can't be contained.

added.title: Plane Excited
added.description: Clarence is all excited visit his grandma when he learns that Chad has never been on a plane. Clarence makes it his mission to help Chad get through a hectic flight.

added.title: Escape from Beyond the Cosmic
added.description: When Clarence accidentally breaks a local arcade game Jeff has become obsessed with, Clarence puts together his own real-life version of the game at home, encouraging Jeff to act out his fantasy in levels created exclusively by Clarence.

added.title: Saturday School
added.description: After creating an unapproved mural on a wall at Aberdale Elementary, Clarence, Jeff and Sumo are forced to come to school on a Saturday to clean up as punishment.

added.title: Attack the Block Party
added.description: Clarence, Jeff and Sumo investigate a high school party down the street, which they mistake for an alien invasion.

added.title: Primo del Arroyo
added.description: Craig lleva a su primo Bryson al Arroyo, donde accidentalmente inicia una guerra de globos de agua.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Bomba apestosa
added.description: La explosión accidental de una bomba de olor causa que todos los niños evacúen el Arroyo, pero Craig toma la responsabilidad de rescatar a aquellos dejados atrás en el hedor.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Guarderia del Arroyo
added.description: Craig y su hermana Jessica intentan administrar la guarderia del Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Entrega Especial
added.description: Enid y Rad salen de viaje en auto para entregar un paquete.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Pijamada en casa de JP
added.description: JP invita a sus amigos para una pijamada, pero resulta ser la misma noche que un gran juego con linternas en el Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La casa de munecas embrujada
added.description: Craig y sus amigos descubren que los persigue una muñeca aterradora y su casa de muñecas embrujada.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Pequena Escuela Madre
added.description: Bienvenidos a la Pequeña Escuela Madre, un lugar en la Tierra donde Gemas de todo el universo pueden aprender a vivir juntas pacíficamente. Pero hay una Gema que se rehúsa a asistir.

added.title: Just Set Up the Chairs
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby get distracted while setting up chairs for a kids birthday party and unleash a monster that terrorizes the entire park.

added.title: Death Punchies
added.description: Rigby learns an ultimate karate move and becomes the bully of the park.

added.title: Meat Your Maker
added.description: After Rigby causes the guys to get locked in a meat locker, he must get help from some hot dogs in order to get them out.

added.title: The Unicorns Have Got to Go
added.description: In order to impress Margret and ask her out, Mordecai hangs with a bunch of punk Unicorns who say they can help him get his lady.

added.title: Don
added.description: Rigby's estranged accountant brother comes back to help save the park from an audit. While everyone loves Don, Rigby wants nothing to do with him.

added.title: Presentando a Joe Kaffi
added.description: K.O. intenta ayudar a Joe Kaffi, su comediante favorito.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Mystery Noise
added.description: It's Sleepover Dream Night in the RV and the gang just wants to get some sleep to dream their dreams, but when a mysterious noise keeps them awake, their grip on sanity begins slipping.

added.title: Perfect Kid
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a kid become perfect by turning him into a robot.  But when the robot tries to destroy him for being imperfect, Uncle Grandpa goes on the run.

added.title: Not Funny
added.description: A young girl's suppressed sense of humor breeds evil that can only be defeated with the help of Uncle Grandpa.

added.title: Prison Break
added.description: When Mr. Gus and Pizza Steve's prank calling lands them in an intergalactic prison, they must work together to escape.

added.title: New Kid
added.description: Uncle Grandpa gives a kid a haircut that is too cool for school.

added.title: Companeros de Cama Extranos
added.description: Tras una batalla demencial, Mao Mao y Cobrangután terminan internados en la misma habitación de hospital. Pero incluso con yesos que les cubren todo el cuerpo, los enemigos declarados siguen peleando.

added.title: Burlate con Todas tus Fuerzas
added.description: Cuando Adorabat empieza a interrumpir agresivamente a todos con su nuevo poder que le da energía, se convierte en una amenaza para el reino entero.

added.title: El Futuro
added.description: Steven por fin está listo para avanzar.
